$Header: /data/zender/nco_20150216/nco/doc/ANNOUNCE,v 1.245 2007-06-28 06:36:01 zender Exp $ -*-text-*-

The netCDF operators NCO version 3.9.0 are ready. 

http://nco.sf.net (Homepage)
http://dust.ess.uci.edu/nco (Homepage "mirror")

Release 3.9.0 supports Lempel-Ziv deflation for netCDF4, 
and contains a fix for building ncap2 with Intel compilers.

Our unscientific testing shows that maximum deflation compresses
typical climate datasets by 30-40%. 
Convert a netCDF3 dataset to a (deflated) netCDF4 dataset:

ncks -O -4 -L 9 in.nc out.nc # Deflate file

Pack then deflate files to save more space:

ncpdq -O -4 -L 9 in.nc out.nc # Pack and deflate file

NB: netCDF4-enabled NCO 3.9.1 must be built with netCDF4
snapshot2007060701 or newer.

0. Thanks to KR for the $50 donation!

A. -L [0..9] deflates (Lempel-Ziv compresses) netCDF4 files 
   http://nco.sf.net/nco.html#deflate

B. --fl_fmt switch supports converting netCDF4->netCDF3
   http://nco.sf.net/nco.html#fl_fmt

C. New Documentation:
   Working with non-standard grids, e.g., 2D grids 
   http://nco.sf.net/nco.html#grd

E. Improve ncap2 missing_value handling and RAM variables (fxm)

F. ncap2 grows more powerful: it supports loops!
   Demonstration scripts ~/nco/data/[bin_cnt.nco,psd_wrf.nco]
   http://nco.sf.net/nco.html#ncap2 

G. Fix bug with ncap2 built with Intel compilers
   Thanks to Remik Ziemlinski for his excellent bug reports!
   http://nco.sf.net#bug_ncbo_pck

H. Pre-built, up-to-date, Debian Sid & Ubuntu binaries are available.
   http://nco.sf.net#debian

I. Pre-built, up-to-date, RPM packages are available.
   http://nco.sf.net#rpm

J. Reminder: NCO support for netCDF4 features is tracked at

   http://nco.sf.net/nco.html#nco4

   To build NCO with netCDF4 support, use 

   export NETCDF4_ROOT=/usr/local/netcdf4 # Set netCDF4 location
   cd ~/nco;./configure --enable-netcdf4  # Configure mechanism -or-
   cd ~/nco/bld;./make NETCDF4=Y allinone # Old Makefile mechanism

Enjoy,
Charlie
 
